1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:11,000
 ovog jutra razmišljaćemo o tome kako zagovarati učinkovito, djelotvorno.

2
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:18,000
 U evanđelju po Mateju 6:7

3
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:27,000
 Kad molite, ne blebećite kao pogani, misle da će snoštva riječi biti uslišani.

4
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:38,000
 Znači, Isus govori da kada molimo, ne koristimo previše riječi.

5
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:51,000
 I On nam kaže, nemojte misliti ako u molitvama koristite mnoštvo riječi, da ćete biti uslišani.

6
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:54,000
 Tako pogani čine.

7
00:00:54,000 --> 00:01:00,000
 Znači, trebamo znati kako moliti.

8
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:06,000
 Učenici su prišli Isusu

9
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:09,000
 dok je On molio

10
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:11,000
 i rekli su mu

11
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:16,000
 u evanđelju po Luki 11:

12
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:21,000
 "Gospodine, nauči nas moliti."

13
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:26,000
 Tako i mi trebamo upitati gospodine,

14
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:31,000
 "Zamoliti ga, gospodine, nauči nas moliti."

15
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:37,000
 So, I am going to give you 12 rules

16
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:40,000
 that are going to help you

17
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:43,000
 in your intercession.

18
00:01:43,000 --> 00:01:56,000
 I have the PowerPoint for you over here.

19
00:01:56,000 --> 00:01:58,000
 Rule number one.

20
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:02,000
 To pray in the power of the Holy Spirit.

21
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:05,000
 Molite u snazi Duha Svetoga.

22
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:08,000
 So, when we pray, when we intercede,

23
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:11,000
 we should intercede in the power of the Holy Spirit.

24
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:22,000
 We think that we know everything.

25
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:28,000
 But the truth is, we do not know anything.

26
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:30,000
 Even when we intercede,

27
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:39,000
 you know, what we see is not what the reality is.

28
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:43,000
 I will give you a simple example.

29
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:49,000
 Once, one of my friends asked me,

30
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:52,000
 "Can you please come home and pray for my daughter

31
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:57,000
 who is preparing for the senior school examination?"

32
00:02:57,000 --> 00:03:10,000
 So, we went to pray.

33
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:15,000
 Two of us from the prayer group.

34
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:20,000
 Two of us from the prayer group.

35
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:22,000
 And as we were praying,

36
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:26,000
 the father, the mother and the two of us and the girl,

37
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:35,000
 the Lord said,

38
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:41,000
 that this girl has a suicidal tendency.

39
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:48,000
 So, we asked the parents.

40
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:53,000
 Yeah, parents said, yes, she tried to commit suicide.

41
00:03:53,000 --> 00:04:05,000
 Now, that has a big impact on her learning, on her studying.

42
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:06,000
 But the parents never disclosed that.

43
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:14,000
 Although they knew this.

44
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:18,000
 So, as we were praying further,

45
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:20,000
 the Lord said,

46
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:21,000
 the Lord said,

47
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:27,000
 you know, when the parents are away at work,

48
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:30,000
 during the day,

49
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:35,000
 there is a boy who is telephoning and disturbing her in her studies.

50
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:47,000
 So, we asked the girl.

51
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:50,000
 She said, yes, that is right.

52
00:04:50,000 --> 00:04:53,000
 a very simple example.

53
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:56,000
 But, to let you know,

54
00:04:56,000 --> 00:04:59,000
 that when we pray for a situation,

55
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:06,000
 we really do not comprehend everything.

56
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:11,000
 There are many hidden things.

57
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:13,000
 sometimes people know,

58
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:18,000
 and they do not tell you.

59
00:05:18,000 --> 00:05:23,000
 Sometimes they themselves do not know.

60
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:30,000
 So, that is why we need to rely on the Holy Spirit.

61
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:38,000
 Romans chapter 8, 26-27.

62
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:49,000
 It says that we do not know how to pray as we ought.

63
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:55,000
 And the Holy Spirit comes to our help.

64
00:05:55,000 --> 00:06:00,000
 So, it is the Holy Spirit who helps us in our intercession.

65
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:05,000
 So, when we pray,

66
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:09,000
 we need to pray in the power of the Holy Spirit.

67
00:06:09,000 --> 00:06:18,000
 I also told you yesterday that intercession is a trinitarian prayer.

68
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:28,000
 We pray in the power of the Holy Spirit.

69
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:33,000
 through Jesus the intercessor.

70
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:39,000
 And our prayers are addressed to the Father.

71
00:06:39,000 --> 00:06:46,000
 So, the Holy Spirit plays a very important role in our intercession.

72
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:59,000
 And that is why we need to use the charisms when we intercede.

73
00:06:59,000 --> 00:07:05,000
 The charisms are very important tools of intercession.

74
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:17,000
 especially the gift of word of knowledge.

75
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:21,000
 The word of wisdom.

76
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:24,000
 The gift of prophecy.

77
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:27,000
 The gift of tongues.

78
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:30,000
 The gift of discernment.

79
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:36,000
 The gift of interpretation of tongues.

80
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:42,000
 So, these are mainly the gifts that help us during our intercession.

81
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:44,000
 Alleluia.

82
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:54,000
 So, we go to rule number two.

83
00:07:54,000 --> 00:08:01,000
 That is to intercede according to God's will.

84
00:08:01,000 --> 00:08:08,000
 In Luke chapter 10.

85
00:08:08,000 --> 00:08:13,000
 41, 42.

86
00:08:13,000 --> 00:08:16,000
 The Lord told Martha.

87
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:17,000
 Martha.

88
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:22,000
 You are worried about many things.

89
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:23,000
 Martha, Martha.

90
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:26,000
 You are worried about many things.

91
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:29,000
 But there is one thing that is required.

92
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:36,000
 That is to sit at the feet at my feet.

93
00:08:36,000 --> 00:08:42,000
 And Mary has chosen the right thing.

94
00:08:42,000 --> 00:08:49,000
 So, sometimes in our intercession we are like Martha.

95
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:53,000
 We are worried about many things.

96
00:08:53,000 --> 00:09:01,000
 Because people have been telephoning and asking us to pray.

97
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:07,000
 People have personally asked us to pray.

98
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:14,000
 People request us to pray through the WhatsApp.

99
00:09:14,000 --> 00:09:17,000
 People send us emails.

100
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:24,000
 So, there are many prayer requests coming.

101
00:09:24,000 --> 00:09:32,000
 So, when we go to intercede, we are like Martha with many, many things.

102
00:09:32,000 --> 00:09:40,000
 But the Lord is telling us, when you come to intercede, just sit at my feet.

103
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:47,000
 Just listen to me.

104
00:09:47,000 --> 00:09:54,000
 Just know what is moving in my heart.

105
00:09:54,000 --> 00:09:57,000
 And that is most important.

106
00:09:57,000 --> 00:10:05,000
 We also know that our prayers are answered when we intercede according to God's will.

107
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:08,000
 We also know that our prayers are always heard when we are in God's will.

108
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:09,000
 We also know that our prayers are always heard when we are in God's will.

109
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:10,000
 We also know that our prayers are always heard when we are in God's will.

110
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:11,000
 Jeremiah 29.11.

111
00:10:11,000 --> 00:10:14,000
 Jeremiah 29.11.

112
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:30,000
 I alone know the plans I have for you.

113
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:42,000
 Plans to bring you prosperity and not disaster.

114
00:10:42,000 --> 00:10:49,000
 Plans to bring about the future you hope for.

115
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:58,000
 And in 1 John 5.14.

116
00:10:58,000 --> 00:11:05,000
 It says, we have this confidence in him.

117
00:11:05,000 --> 00:11:14,000
 That if we ask anything according to his will.

118
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:16,000
 He hears us.

119
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:19,000
 We saw this yesterday.

120
00:11:19,000 --> 00:11:28,000
 So, whenever we pray, we need to pray according to God's will.

121
00:11:28,000 --> 00:11:31,000
 So, when I say this.

122
00:11:31,000 --> 00:11:39,000
 You should not think that we should not pray for people who ask us for prayers.

123
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:46,000
 Yes, we should pray for them.

124
00:11:46,000 --> 00:11:51,000
 At the same time, we should also pray according to God's will.

125
00:11:51,000 --> 00:12:03,000
 Because the Lord is looking for intercessors.

126
00:12:03,000 --> 00:12:13,000
 I have seen that the Lord speaks to us and the Lord answers our prayers when we intercede according to his will.

127
00:12:13,000 --> 00:12:29,000
 I want to share with you an experience, one of our first experiences in prophetic intercession.

128
00:12:29,000 --> 00:12:32,000
 This was in the year 1996.

129
00:12:32,000 --> 00:12:57,000
 We had a small group of 12 people who used to come together every Saturday and pray.

130
00:12:57,000 --> 00:13:04,000
 So, normally we used to pray for some time and wait upon the Lord.

131
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:16,000
 Asking the Lord to speak to us.

132
00:13:16,000 --> 00:13:20,000
 So, that Saturday when we were asking the Lord what to pray.

133
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:27,000
 The Lord gave us a vision.

134
00:13:27,000 --> 00:13:33,000
 That vision was a cyclone coming towards coastal India.

135
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:48,000
 And this cyclone was coming towards the cost of India.

136
00:13:48,000 --> 00:13:54,000
 So, we just prayed during that time.

137
00:13:54,000 --> 00:14:01,000
 The next week when we came together again.

138
00:14:01,000 --> 00:14:05,000
 The next week when we came together again.

139
00:14:05,000 --> 00:14:09,000
 The Lord gave us the same vision.

140
00:14:09,000 --> 00:14:11,000
 The same cyclone.

141
00:14:11,000 --> 00:14:13,000
 So, we prayed again.

142
00:14:13,000 --> 00:14:14,000
 The next day.

143
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:15,000
 The next day.

144
00:14:15,000 --> 00:14:20,000
 The news started coming on the television channel.

145
00:14:20,000 --> 00:14:28,000
 That there is going to be a cyclone coming towards coastal India.

146
00:14:28,000 --> 00:14:35,000
 In a way we were very excited.

147
00:14:35,000 --> 00:14:39,000
 Because the Lord spoke to us eight days in advance.

148
00:14:39,000 --> 00:14:46,000
 The Lord spoke to us eight days in advance.

149
00:14:46,000 --> 00:14:52,000
 So, the Lord had told that there is going to be a cyclone coming to India.

150
00:14:52,000 --> 00:14:59,000
 So, we telephoned to the people around us.

151
00:14:59,000 --> 00:15:05,000
 Asking them to pray for the cyclone.

152
00:15:05,000 --> 00:15:12,000
 And some of us spent the night praying for the cyclone.

153
00:15:12,000 --> 00:15:27,000
 Now, the speed of the cyclone was 150 kilometers per hour.

154
00:15:27,000 --> 00:15:37,000
 So, the cyclone was going to hit next day morning at 8 AM.

155
00:15:37,000 --> 00:15:40,000
 But, in the morning, the news came.

156
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:49,000
 The speed of the cyclone is reduced from 150 kilometers to 80 kilometers per hour.

157
00:15:49,000 --> 00:15:57,000
 The speed of the cyclone is reduced from 150 kilometers to 80 kilometers per hour.

158
00:15:57,000 --> 00:16:00,000
 And the cyclone is going to be delayed.

159
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:10,000
 And we continued to pray.

160
00:16:10,000 --> 00:16:12,000
 So, in the evening, the news came.

161
00:16:12,000 --> 00:16:22,000
 That the speed of the cyclone is reduced from 80 kilometers to 8 kilometers per hour.

162
00:16:22,000 --> 00:16:37,000
 And the next day, in the evening, we had a commentary on the cyclone.

163
00:16:37,000 --> 00:16:47,000
 On the next day, in the evening, we had a commentary on the cyclone.

164
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:56,000
 Somebody from the weather department was commenting on the cyclone.

165
00:16:56,000 --> 00:17:07,000
 He said the cyclone had come 200 kilometers near to the coastal India.

166
00:17:07,000 --> 00:17:17,000
 So, it would have taken little more than one hour for the cyclone to hit.

167
00:17:17,000 --> 00:17:24,000
 But the cyclone, according to him, moved back to the sea.

168
00:17:24,000 --> 00:17:30,000
 And he said the cyclone is stationed in one place.

169
00:17:30,000 --> 00:17:37,000
 And he said, this is a very strange phenomenon.

170
00:17:37,000 --> 00:17:39,000
 And he said, this is a very strange phenomenon.

171
00:17:39,000 --> 00:17:55,000
 So, when we heard this, we were very excited.

172
00:17:55,000 --> 00:18:00,000
 You know, the hair on our bodies stood up.

173
00:18:00,000 --> 00:18:19,000
 Because we knew that this cyclone moving back to the sea and being stationed there was because of the power of intercession.

174
00:18:19,000 --> 00:18:26,000
 But the one who was giving the commentary did not understand.

175
00:18:26,000 --> 00:18:32,000
 So, he said, this is something strange.

176
00:18:32,000 --> 00:18:46,000
 So, we intercessors, when we intercede according to God's will,

177
00:18:46,000 --> 00:18:53,000
 strange and powerful things happen.

178
00:18:53,000 --> 00:19:07,000
 So, let us learn more and more to intercede according to God's will.

179
00:19:07,000 --> 00:19:16,000
 So, you need to remember these rules because I will ask you after some time.

180
00:19:16,000 --> 00:19:21,000
 Now, we are going to rule number three.

181
00:19:21,000 --> 00:19:29,000
 Rule number three is to intercede with vision.

182
00:19:29,000 --> 00:19:41,000
 You know, one thing Jesus said is to watch and pray.

183
00:19:41,000 --> 00:19:47,000
 Watch and pray.

184
00:19:47,000 --> 00:19:53,000
 That is a very important principle.

185
00:19:53,000 --> 00:20:00,000
 He said, don't close your eyes, sit there and pray.

186
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:02,000
 Look around.

187
00:20:02,000 --> 00:20:05,000
 Watch and pray.

188
00:20:05,000 --> 00:20:10,000
 I also spoke to you about reading the signs of the time.

189
00:20:10,000 --> 00:20:21,000
 And more than this, what Jesus is telling us is this.

190
00:20:21,000 --> 00:20:27,000
 What should be our vision when we pray?

191
00:20:27,000 --> 00:20:30,000
 We should have a vision.

192
00:20:30,000 --> 00:20:34,000
 I gave you the example of the second mason.

193
00:20:34,000 --> 00:20:44,000
 And when you compare the second mason with the first mason,

194
00:20:44,000 --> 00:20:51,000
 The first mason had a limited vision.

195
00:20:51,000 --> 00:20:56,000
 But the second mason had a much wider vision.

196
00:20:56,000 --> 00:21:03,000
 And we should be like the second mason.

197
00:21:03,000 --> 00:21:16,000
 So, we should intercede with a vision for what we want to achieve.

198
00:21:16,000 --> 00:21:18,000
 It's Proverbs.

199
00:21:18,000 --> 00:21:29,000
 Proverbs 29:18 says,

200
00:21:29,000 --> 00:21:38,000
 If you do not have vision, then people get demoralized.

201
00:21:38,000 --> 00:21:43,000
 People perish.

202
00:21:43,000 --> 00:21:48,000
 So, most of the time, in our intercessory groups,

203
00:21:48,000 --> 00:21:53,000
 We are very selves and good people.

204
00:21:53,000 --> 00:21:57,000
 We are very selves and good people.

205
00:21:57,000 --> 00:22:05,000
 We come together and we pray.

206
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:07,000
 That is very good.

207
00:22:07,000 --> 00:22:13,000
 But many a time, we do not have any vision.

208
00:22:13,000 --> 00:22:21,000
 What is that you want to achieve through your intercession?

209
00:22:21,000 --> 00:22:26,000
 Are we like the first mason?

210
00:22:26,000 --> 00:22:32,000
 But we should have a much, much wider vision.

211
00:22:32,000 --> 00:22:45,000
 You know, sister Anne Shields, when she writes about intercession,

212
00:22:45,000 --> 00:22:53,000
 She says, the ultimate goal for which we always intercede should be,

213
00:22:53,000 --> 00:23:03,000
 Amen! Come, Lord Jesus!

214
00:23:03,000 --> 00:23:11,000
 So, we should intercede for the coming of God's kingdom.

215
00:23:11,000 --> 00:23:18,000
 We should intercede for the salvation of souls.

216
00:23:18,000 --> 00:23:28,000
 We should intercede for winning over our cities and our countries.

217
00:23:28,000 --> 00:23:35,000
 You know, yesterday one of the groups, when they reported, they said,

218
00:23:35,000 --> 00:23:42,000
 And the person was quite sad when he reported.

219
00:23:42,000 --> 00:23:46,000
 The person was quite sad when he reported.

220
00:23:46,000 --> 00:23:54,000
 That many of our clergy think that what they do is just a profession.

221
00:23:54,000 --> 00:24:09,000
 And then they said that they prayed for the strongholds to be broken.

222
00:24:09,000 --> 00:24:13,000
 And they said that they prayed for the strongholds.

223
00:24:13,000 --> 00:24:24,000
 In fact, they went in for a kind of a deliverance in that.

224
00:24:24,000 --> 00:24:29,000
 So, that is interceding with a vision.

225
00:24:29,000 --> 00:24:36,000
 For example, if you are interceding for Croatia.

226
00:24:36,000 --> 00:24:39,000
 What are we interceding for?

227
00:24:39,000 --> 00:24:46,000
 We should be interceding that the Lord break all these strongholds.

228
00:24:46,000 --> 00:24:52,000
 All the bondages.

229
00:24:52,000 --> 00:24:59,000
 All the curses of the past.

230
00:24:59,000 --> 00:25:03,000
 All the wounds of the past.

231
00:25:03,000 --> 00:25:07,000
 And heal this nation.

232
00:25:07,000 --> 00:25:14,000
 It's only you and I who can set this nation free.

233
00:25:14,000 --> 00:25:22,000
 You know, when I was reading about Croatia.

234
00:25:22,000 --> 00:25:25,000
 I felt very sad.

235
00:25:25,000 --> 00:25:32,000
 Because this nation has passed through a lot of atrocities.

236
00:25:32,000 --> 00:25:39,000
 A lot of persecution.

237
00:25:39,000 --> 00:25:42,000
 A lot of genocide.

238
00:25:42,000 --> 00:25:44,000
 A lot of genocide.

239
00:25:44,000 --> 00:25:49,000
 There were hundreds of priests being killed.

240
00:25:49,000 --> 00:25:53,000
 And there was a lot of oppression on this nation.

241
00:25:53,000 --> 00:25:58,000
 During the Ottoman rule.

242
00:25:58,000 --> 00:26:07,000
 During the Austria-Hungarian rule.

243
00:26:07,000 --> 00:26:13,000
 During the communist regime.

244
00:26:13,000 --> 00:26:18,000
 During your war of independence.

245
00:26:18,000 --> 00:26:23,000
 So, in a way, our nations are wounded.

246
00:26:23,000 --> 00:26:30,000
 And who will set our nation free?

247
00:26:30,000 --> 00:26:40,000
 Now, are you going to intercede all the time for just one person who is admitted in the hospital?

248
00:26:40,000 --> 00:26:52,000
 Are you going to intercede all the time for one person who is appearing for an interview for the job?

249
00:26:52,000 --> 00:27:03,000
 Don't you have a responsibility to pray for the millions of people whose wounds are still fresh?

